<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD4FFBFFF7BF857FC3CF853" blockId="104.[189,1399,1888,2025]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFD4FFBFFF7BF857FEF3F81E" author="Ceuca T." box="[189,350,1930,1957]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" pagination="35 - 46" refId="ref34309" refString="Ceuca T. 1985. Diplopodes nouveaux dans la faune de la Roumanie (Diplopoda - Ascospermophora). Studia Universitatis Babes-Bolyai Biologia 30: 35 - 46." type="journal article" year="1985">Ceuca (1985)</bibRefCitation>
gave the 
<typeStatus id="5D0F881CFFD4FFBFFE15F857FDABF81E" box="[467,518,1931,1957]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
locality as “la forêt de Slătioara, située au nord de notre pays”. There are several places of that name in northern 
<collectingCountry id="FAA3762EFFD4FFBFFD50F876FCAEF87F" box="[662,771,1962,1988]" name="Romania" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Romania</collectingCountry>
, but the 
<typeStatus id="5D0F881CFFD4FFBFFCAAF877FC32F87E" box="[876,927,1963,1989]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">type</typeStatus>
locality is tentatively interpreted as the village Slătioara in Strâmtura Commune, 
<collectingRegion id="4070F85CFFD4FFBFFD61F813FC21F853" box="[679,908,1998,2025]" country="Romania" name="Maramures" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Maramures County</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
